<HEADLINE> Aircraft Rescue For Flood Victims In Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China's State Flood Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters has sent two aircraft to areas flooded
by the Nenjiang River and its tributaries in northeastern China to
provide relief for more than 1,000 people who have been trapped by
the flooding.
</P>
<P>
Large quantities of relief goods have been transported to the
flooded areas, according to the headquarters, which says that no
casualties have been reported so far.
</P>
<P>
This year's flood on Nenjiang is the largest on record, with
water levels having surpassed the danger level, affecting
localities of Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Heilongjiang and
Kirin provinces. They are expected to hit record highs on
Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
