<HEADLINE> Pantani Wins 15th Stage in Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Italian Marco Pantani, riding for
Marcatone Uno, won the 15th stage of the Tour de France cycling
race on Monday, a 189 kilometers run from Grenoble to Les Deux
Alpes.
</P>
<P>
Pantani reached the finishing line with a time of five hours
43 minutes and 45 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Following the stage's victory, the Italian also took the
yellow jersey from last year's race winner Jan Ullrich of Germany
and has an advantage of almost four minutes on Bobby Julich of the
united states.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich lost almost half a minute changing tyres in the stage.
</P>
</TEXT>
