<HEADLINE> Turkmenistan FM to Visit France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The foreign minister of Turkmenistan
Boris Shikhmuradov will pay an official visit to France on Tuesday
at the invitation of his French counterpart Hubert Vedrine, said
the French Foreign Ministry on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Shikhmuradov and Vedrine will focus their talks on the
situation in Afghanistan, the peace process in Tajikistan and
exploitation of the rich oil and gas resources of the Caspian Sea,
said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
France recently called on all the neighboring countries of
Afghanistan to reach an agreement on help end the two-decade wars
in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers are also expected to discuss a number of
contracts of economic cooperation between France and Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
French enterprises are involved in a number of projects in
Turkmenistan, including the modernization of a refinery, the
construction of a parliament building and an airport, and the
development the television network of the Central Asia country.
</P>
<P>
French oil companies are also interested in Turkmenistan's rich
oil and gas resources.
</P>
<P>
Turkmanistan President Saparmurat Niyazov visited France in
September 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
