<HEADLINE> Istanbul Stock Exchange Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Istanbul Stock Exchange
National-100 Index closed higher Monday at 4,326.11 points, up
56.11 points, or 1.34 percent, from that on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The market was closed on Saturday and Sunday. Monday's trading
was hectic with the turnover reaching 85 trillion Turkish liras
(over 315 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The financial index closed at 5,314.74 points, up 75.61 points,
or 1.46 percent, the industrial index closed at 3,700.97 points,
up 47.78 points, or 1.33 percent, and the service index closed at
5,069.86 points, up 23.10 points, or 0.49 percent, from Friday's
finishes. 
</P>
