<HEADLINE> U.S. Finances Ugandan Human Rights Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. government has extended
a grant of 50,000 U.S. Dollars for three human rights projects in
Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The beneficiaries are the Uganda Prisoners Aid Foundation,
Mbarara District Women's Development Association and
Uganda Gender Resource Center (UGRC), Radio Uganda reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony of the agreement, U.S. Ambassador to
Uganda, Nancy Powell, said her government was committed to the
promotion of human rights and democracy in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Uganda Prisoners Aid Foundation hoped the
money will go a long way in enhancing their programs.
</P>
<P>
Hope Mwesigye, the chairperson of UGRC, said the grant will be
used in conducting para-legal programs aimed at sensitizing women
to their rights, violence against women and property rights.
</P>
