<HEADLINE> France Calls on Guinea Bissau Parties to Respect Truce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- France Monday called on the two
conflicting sides of Guinea-Bissau to do everything to seize the
chance of a political solution after they reached a truce Sunday
under mediation of Portuguese-speaking countries.
</P>
<P>
"France calls for the success of the talks which should begin
soon with the aim of a lasting ceasefire agreement," said French
Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
The representatives of the government and rebellious soldiers
have agreed to stay at their present positions and create a
humanitarian corridor to allow aid go to the 250,000 civilians who
were forced to flee home by the fighting which began on June 7.
</P>
<P>
"France calls on the signatories of the memorandum to respect
the terms of the truce they have concluded, as well as to do all
to seize the chance which offers itself for a peaceful solution to
the crisis," said the spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
She also praised Portuguese speaking countries for the efforts
they deployed after Guinea-Bissau. 
</P>
</TEXT>
