<HEADLINE> Role of Resources in U.N. Council's Work Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Mobilization of resources
and promotion of international cooperation should form the core
work of the U.N. Economic and Social Council (ECOSOC), Deputy
Chinese Representative to the U.N. Shen Guofang said here on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Adequate resources are an essential prerequisite for successful
follow-up to major international conferences, he told an ECOSOC
session.
</P>
<P>
Shen said it is necessary to strengthen coordination between
the council and U.N. funds and agencies, including the Bretton-
woods institutions.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, if the trend of weakening international
cooperation and the steady decline of official development
assistance (ODC) cannot be reversed, then coordination alone is
not going to produce miracles.
</P>
<P>
Because of different conditions and development priorities,
U.N. operational activities for development should take full
account of the conditions of the countries concerned and provide
assistance under the guidance of the governments, he stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
