<HEADLINE> Hun Sen's Party Appears Set to Win Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Incumbent Co-Premier Hun Sen's
Cambodian People's Party (CPP) appeared set to win Sunday's
multi-party general elections, according to initial results
provided by the opposition Sam Rainsy Party Monday.
</P>
<P>
The CPP collected 50 seats in the 122-seat National Assembly,
to be followed by ousted First Prime Minister Prince Norodom
Ranariddh's Funcinpec with 43 seats and former Finance Minister
Sam Rainsy's Sam Rainsy Party with 29 seats, Sam Rainsy Party said.
</P>
<P>
However, official initial results have not yet been announced
and are expected to be made public several days later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
