<HEADLINE> Gold Output Falls in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARAE, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's gold production averaged
1.93 tons a month in the first five months of the year as against
2.02 tons last year, Zimbabwe's First Merchant Bank said Monday.eE
</P>
<P>
In an economic bulletin, the bank said the fall reflected
viability problems facing the country's mining industry owing to
low mineral prices and rising production costs.
</P>
<P>
"Output figures have fallen with the closure of several gold
mines and more are expected to cease operation in the next few
months as a result of the disappointing drift in gold prices,"
the bank said.
</P>
<P>
The gold price was quoted at 290.60 U.S.Dollars an ounce in
early Monday trade in Harare.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe is Africa's third largest gold producer after Ghana
and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The mineral contributes about 25 percent to the country's
export earnings.  
</P>
</TEXT>
