<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest commercial bank
Deutsche Bank said Monday its pre-tax profits increased by 65.9
percent to 4.6 billion marks (2.58 billion U.S. dollars) for the
first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the bank, based in Frankfurt, its trading result
in share and bond dealings was up 22 percent to 2.5 billion marks
(1.4 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The bank said the financial crisis in Asia did not result in an
increase in its 1.5 billion mark (around 800 million dollar) risk
provisions for that region. It just re-allocated the funds.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the bank announced that it has decided not to set
up its own insurance company as originally envisaged, but only
sell policies in cooperation with other companies. 
