<HEADLINE> Annan Appoints New UNEP Deputy Executive Director </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Monday appointed Pakistn's former High Commissioner to
Kenya, Shafqzat kakakhel, as Deputy Executive Director of the
United Nations Environmental Program (UNEP), effective on
August 1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Mr. kakakhel is a career diplomat and joined Pakistan's Foreign
Service in 1969. After serving in Pakistan's mission in Lebanon,
Egypt, Germany and India, he was appointed High Commissioner of
Pakistan to Kenya and Uganda and non-resident Ambassador to
Ethiopia and Rwanda in November, 1994.
</P>
<P>
Well versed in environmental affairs, Mr. Kakakhel has served
as Pakistan's Permanent Representative to UNEP and the UN Center
for Human Settlement (Habitat) since his arrival in Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, he was elected President of he eighteenth session of
UNEP's Governing Council, and in 1996, made chairman of Committee
I of Habitat II, held in Istanbul in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Born in 1944, Mr. Kakakhel holds a Masters in Political Science
ans Economic from Peshawar University, Pakistan.  
</P>
