<HEADLINE> Heat Wave Hits Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A heat wave, the second within a
month, is on Monday hitting Greece with temperatures soaring to 38
degrees centigrade in many parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Greece's National Meteorological Service (EMY) said that for
the next two days, temperatures would reach over 40 degrees in
parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
To deal with possible problems stemming from the hot weather,
Greece has placed its hospitals and ambulance services on alert.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry also advised citizens to avoid unnecessary
travelling, stay out of sun and refrain from indulging in heavy
meals and alcoholic drinks.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, a heat wave, which was caused by an inflow
of hot air from northern Africa and lasted almost a week, killed
at least four people in Greece.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, hundreds of firemen, troops and local residents
backed by firefighting planes were Monday battling to control ten
forest fires nationwidely caused by hot weather. 
</P>
</TEXT>
