<HEADLINE> French FM to Visit Iran in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 28 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine will visit Iran next month in a bid to normalize troubled
bilateral ties, the French Foreign Ministry said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 15 members of the European Union (EU), including France,
cut "critical dialogue" with Iran in April 1997 after Germany
accused Iran of being involved in a murder.
</P>
<P>
"This visit comes in the process of normalization of
Franco-Iranian and European-Iranian relations," said Foreign
Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
Ties with Iran thawed when the ban on the exchange of
ministerial visits was lifted in February, following the return of
European ambassadors to Teheran, she said.
</P>
<P>
During the trip on August 22-23, Vedrine will discuss with his
Iranian counterpart Kamal Kharazi many important issues, including
the non-proliferation of weapons of mass destruction, she said.
</P>
<P>
"We hope to have a normal and global political dialogue with a
state that is extremely important, whose place is major in the
Middle East," she added. 
</P>
