<HEADLINE> Chinese Government Shows Concern Over Chinese Indonesians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government is
strongly concerned about the suffering of Indonesians of Chinese
descent and disturbed by the riots in Indonesia in May, according
to Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang Guoqiang.
</P>
<P>
Tang, in answering reporters' questions, said that the Chinese
government has asked the Indonesian government repeatedly through
diplomatic channels for a thorough investigation of the events
surrounding the rape of Chinese Indonesian women during the
turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Steps need to be taken to avoid such misfortunes happening
again in the future, he said, pointing out that Chinese
Indonesians have made important contributions to the economic and
social development of Indonesia with their hard work.
</P>
<P>
He said that their personal safety and legal rights should be
protected by the Indonesian government so they can lead a happy
life along with the Indonesian people.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that dealing with the problem concerning Indonesians
of Chinese descent properly and fairly would benefit the stability
and development of Indonesia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
