<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Hopes Indonesian Situation to Stabilize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan expressed the hope here Tuesday that the situation in
Indonesia will soon stabilize and the country's economy get out of
difficulty as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese Indonesians, as a member of the Indonesian family,
have over the years worked hard and have made important
contributions to Indonesia's economic development and social
stability," Tang said while meeting with Indonesian Foreign
Minister Ali Alatas.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers exchanged views on the relations between
their two countries and matters of mutual concern, according to a
spokeswoman of the Chinese Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the riots in Indonesia in May, Tang noted that "the
unfortunate incident has aroused concern in the international
community and China has also been concerned over the matter."
</P>
<P>
He urged that the legitimate rights and interests of the
Chinese Indonesians, just as those of other citizens in the
country, should be protected by the Indonesian government.
</P>
<P>
"We hope the Indonesian government attaches importance to the
current developments and adopts earnest measures to deal with
them," Tang was quoted by the spokeswoman as saying.
</P>
<P>
He asked the Indonesian government to prevent the recurrence of
such incidents in order to realize peace and unity among various
ethnic groups in the country and promote the country's
development.
</P>
<P>
Alatas expressed the Indonesian government's appreciation of
the sympathy and support provided by the Chinese government when
Indonesia is in difficulty.
</P>
<P>
As a friend, he said, China has given valuable assistance to
Indonesia when it itself has also been affected by the financial
crisis and he expressed heartfelt thanks for this.
</P>
<P>
Alatas said that Chinese Indonesians suffered attacks and
robberies in the social turmoil in May and the Indonesian
government regrets what happened at that time.
</P>
<P>
The new Indonesian government under President Habibie has
strongly condemned such acts and ordered the formation of a
special committee to conduct thorough investigations into them so
as to bring the criminals to justice and make sure that these
incidents would not happen again.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers are here attending the ASEAN
Ministerial Meeting, the ASEAN Regional Forum and the
Post-Ministerial Conference. 
</P>
