Moldova to its partners in the CIS, which is formed by 12 member
states of the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
Russia was the biggest trade partner of Moldova, followed by
Ukraine, Belarus and non-CIS Romania, local daily Curierul
National reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In the January-May period, Moldova's export volume reached 304
million dollars, down 1 percent over the same period last year,
while imports amounted to 491 million, a year-on-year increase of
6 percent, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit of the nation has increased 33 million
dollars to 187 million compared with the same period last year, it
said. 
