of Jiujiang had gone to the Saicheng Lake at midnight on July 25
to check on the flood situation, and, to their surprise, found
nobody manning and patroling the embankments, and what was worse,
water had begun to run over some sections. The five officials were
the very people who were held responsible for flood control
efforts in the area.
</P>
<P>
In related developments, the Party Committee of Enping city in
south China's Guangdong Province, decided on Monday to dismiss
Huang Hanliang from his post as deputy director of the city's
Organization Department and Party secretary of the Personnel
Department. Huang and his family fled the city in a car at a time
when local flood control work had reached its most
frantic. Another official who fled with Huang was given a serious
Party disciplinary warning.  
