<HEADLINE> China's Real Estate Sector Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- China's real estate index, which
indicates the industry's health, was 102.9 in the January-June
period, up 4.7 points from the same period last year, the State
Statistics Bureau and the China Business Climate Monitoring Center
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The bureau attributes the rise to increased investment, an
improved investment structure, and housing sales.
</P>
<P>
The country's index for paid-in investment, land sales, land
development, real estate project completions, and real estate
prices increased.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months, paid-in investment was 150 billion
yuan, up 18.1 percent on a year-on-year basis and 13.67 million
sq.m. of land was developed, up 4.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Apartment prices increased to 2,205 yuan on average per sq.m,
up 10.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The bureau predicts that real estate will do even better in the
second half. 
</P>
