<HEADLINE> Naoki Soma Declared AFC's Player of June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Naoki Soma of Japan's
Kashima Antlers has been declared player of the month for June by
the Asian Football Confederation (AFC), it said in a statement
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Soma, 27, who plays for Japan in the midfield, showed good
form when Japan appeared in its first ever World Cup finals last
month.
</P>
<P>
In the Statement, the AFC said: "Although team-mate Hidetoshi
Nakata received most of the media attention, it was Soma who had
many observers impressed by the quality of his play."
</P>
<P>
Iran's Jalal Talebi, won the Motorola Coach of the month award
following the impressive performance by the Iranian team at the
recent World Cup.
</P>
<P>
The statement noted that the Iranians proved under his
leadership that they are a nation that is continuing to grow as an
Asian football force.
</P>
<P>
China's Ma Mingyu clinched the Amstel Goal of the Month award
for his exceptional strike against South Korea in a pre-World Cup
friendly. 
</P>
