<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Elect Deputies to District People's Congresses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Deputies of the new term of the
people's congress at district and county level of Beijing will be
elected by the end this year, according to a decision made at the
fourth meeting of the Standing Committee of the Beijing Municipal
People's Congress today.
</P>
<P>
More than 8 million voters will then elect the new deputies by
means of voting. Those who will participate in the election also
include the Chinese Communist Party and state leaders living in
Beijing, personnel of Beijing-based central institutions, and
People's Liberation Army troops stationed in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
According to the electoral method, candidates of deputies to
the district and country's people's congresses will be selected
through nomination by constituencies.
</P>
<P>
Political parties, people's organizations and a group of more
than ten voters are also eligible to recommend candidates. The
number of official candidates must be one-third to 100 percent
more than that of deputies to be elected.
</P>
<P>
Based on Beijing's permanent population, the new term of
people's congress at the district and county level will include
4,403 deputies, which are 506 persons less than the previous term.
</P>
<P>
Preparations for the election are now under way. The election,
including publicity, registration of voters, nomination and
casting ballots, is expected to be launched in October.  
</P>
</TEXT>
