<HEADLINE> Stolle Steps In as Enqvist Withdraws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
WASHINGTON, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Sandon Stolle of Australia
stepped in as Thomas Enqvist of Sweden pulled out in the last
minute, and beat Taylor Dent of the United States on Monday in
the Mercedes Cup tennis tournament in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
Fourth-seeded Enqvist withdrew for tendinitis of the right
ankle about three hours before the match.
</P>
<P>
Stolle took over his place to play the scheduled first round
match against the 17-year-old American amateur, winning 6-3, 6-2
in just 55 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The world number one Pete Sampras of the United States pulled
out on Friday for recovering from minor surgery to repair an
injury to the bottom of his right foot on July 15.
</P>
<P>
His top seed was taken over by Australian Patrick Rafter who
is to meet Ramon Delgado of Paraguay on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Fifth seed American Andre Agassi was seeking for his fourth
title the season as he is to face newcomer American Bob Bryan in
another Tuesday night's matchup.
</P>
<P>
In Monday's other matches, Seventh-seeded Byron Black of
Zimbabwe fought off three set points in the second set to dispose
of Dutch Sjent Schalken 6-4, 7-6 (10-8).
</P>
<P>
Black's younger brother Wayne did not survived a three-set
match when he was beaten by Martin Damm of the Czech Republic 2-6,
7-5, 6-1. 
</P>
