<HEADLINE> Vajpayee Gov't Fails on All Fronts: Sonia Gandhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Sonia Gandhi, president of the
Congress party, the biggest opposition party in India, Tuesday
severely attacked the BJP-led Vajpayee government for its failure
of governance on all fronts in the country since it came to power
on March 19 this year.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a mass rally here signaling the beginning of the
party's agitation against the government, Sonia Gandhi said that
the "directionless" policies of the government had caused
skyrocketing prices of essential commodities and deteriorating law
and order situation in the country, hitting the common man hard.
</P>
<P>
The government was only busy in grappling with its internal
differences and it has neither the time nor sympathy for the
helpless people, she said.
</P>
<P>
In a ten-minute fiery speech, she especially targeted the
deteriorating law and order situation and shortage of drinking
water and electricity in New Delhi, capital of India. She said,
"How can the people, who cannot even handle the affairs of the
national capital, look after the entire nation?"
</P>
<P>
The situation in the country has worsened in the recent months
with farmers in various parts of the country committing suicide
and communal tension, atrocities against women and attempts to
encroach on the rights of Dalits (lower castes in India) rising.
With the advent of the Vajpayee government the entire economic and
law and order situation in the country has worsened, she further
said.
</P>
<P>
The Congress alone could provide a progressive pro-poor and a
just government, she said adding that the party was not hungry for
power.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the rally, she marched to the Rashtrapati Bhavan
(President Palace) to submit a memorandum to the president against
the failure of the Vajpayee government.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, all opposition parties in both houses of
Parliament on Tuesday launched a scathing attack on the BJP-led
coalition government for its total failure of governance on all
fronts, especially on the law and order situation and rising
prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
