<HEADLINE> Southern Development Zone Attracting Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The Economic and Technological
Development Zone in Guangzhou, the capital of south China's
Guangdong Province, got 250 million U.S. dollars worth of foreign
funds in the first half of this year, a 25 percent increase from
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The zone has attracted 1.9 billion dollar-worth of foreign
investment since it was established in December 1984. Its
businesses are mainly export-oriented industries. Three-fourths of
the companies are technology-intensive.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of the year, its total exports were worth 277
million dollars, 33.8 percent more than for the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
And, 48 of the world's top 500 multinationals have offices
here. This year, for the first time, Spanish and Turkish investors
opened offices in the zone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
