<HEADLINE> Indian Opposition Parties Criticize Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 28 (Xinhua) -- India's entire Opposition
parties Tuesday staged a noisy walkout from the ongoing session
of the Lower House of Parliament, severely criticizing the total
failure of the government especially on the law and order and
price fronts in the country.
</P>
<P>
Coinciding with the launching of President Sonia Gandhi's first
agitational program of the Congress, the biggest Opposition in the
country, here Tuesday, leader of the Opposition in the House
Sharad Pawr raised the issue during the zero hour questioning the
government's moral justification to continue in office.
</P>
<P>
The law and order situation has worsened throughout the country
and the government has failed on this front. The miseries of the
people had increased manifold ever since the BJP-led coalition
government came to power since March 19. The government had
promised stringent action against hoarders and blackmarketeers
during a special discussion on the price situation to bring prices
down but nothing has been done in this regard, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Vajpayee government's attitude was very callous towards the
people's plight and thus it had no right to continue in office, he
further said.
</P>
<P>
The Opposition in the Upper House of Parliament Tuesday also
blasted the government for what it termed as the latter's failure
to contain unbridled rise in prices of essential commodities and
attributed the inflationary trend to economic sanctions imposed
against India after it conducted nuclear tests in mid-May.
</P>
</TEXT>
