<HEADLINE> Rafter Heads Australian Davis Cup Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
CANBERRA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Open champion Patrick
 Rafter heads a six-man Australian squad named on Tuesday for
 the Davis Cup World Group qualifying tie against Uzbekistan in
 September, according to reports from Sydney.
</P>
<P>
 Rafter, Jason Stoltenberg, Mark Woodforde, Todd Woodbridge,
 Scott Draper and Lleyton Hewitt were named by captain John
 Newcombe for the September 25-27 tie in the northern Queensland
 state town of Townsville.
</P>
<P>
 The result of September's competition will determine
 whether Australia remain in the elite World Group of the Davis
 Cup in 1999.
</P>
<P>
 Teams beaten in the World Group first round must win a
 qualifying tie to avoid falling back into regional groupings.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
