<HEADLINE> Annual Hong Kong Food Festival to Feast Gourmets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Tourist
Association (HKTA) announced Tuesday that famed Hong Kong chefs
would feast visitors during the annual Food Festival next month.
</P>
<P>
The 16-day event starting August 8 will be organized by the
HKTA, the 13th in the annual series since 1986. This year's event
means something special as it serves as part of HKTA's desperate
efforts to boost local tourist industry at a time when Hong Kong
has been struck by the regional economic turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Featuring in the "mouth-watering" festival, described by HKTA
officials at a press conference here Tuesday, will be eight
programs including special culinary tours, cooking classes with
some of Hong Kong's best chefs and district-wide food festival,
street parties and the ever-popular Hong Kong waiters' race and
food bazaar.
</P>
<P>
The race, jointly organized by the HKTA and the Hong Kong
Hotels Association, is a core program of the festival and it
provides a fun-packed day featuring "Food, Excitement and
Entertainment".
</P>
<P>
The festival celebrates the cornucopia of first-class cuisine
available in the City of Life, showcasing both the overwhelming
wonder of Chinese regional cuisine and the very best of almost
everywhere else in the world.
</P>
<P>
The scores of outstanding restaurants and hotels participating
in the festival will offer special menus to mark the event,
including the award-winning ones from the previous food festivals.
</P>
<P>
"From the diversity of Chinese regional cooking to the tastes
and flavors of food from all corners of the globe, Hong Kong has
gained worldwide recognition as a dining paradise," said Douglas
Gautier, deputy director of the HKTA.
</P>
<P>
He described the event as "one of the most anticipated and
popular events on Hong Kong's calendar." 
</P>
</TEXT>
