<HEADLINE> EU Backs Syria's Sovereignty Over Golan Heights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) envoy for
the Mideast peace has said that Syrian sovereignty over the
occupied Golan Heights must be restored so as to achieve a
comprehensive regional peace.
</P>
<P>
Miguel Angel Moratinos made the remarks here Monday night in
talks with Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq Al-Sharaa, in which the
two officials discussed the stalled Mideast peace process due to
Israel's intransigence, the Al Baath newspaper said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian-Israeli peace talks have been stalled since early
1996. The two countries have so far failed to bridge their gap
over the future of the Golan Heights captured by Israel from Syria
in the 1967 Middle East War.
</P>
<P>
Syrian President Hafez Al-Assad has said Damascus will not
resume talks with Israel unless it agreed to return the Golan
Heights.
</P>
<P>
In an interview Monday with Orient Radio, Moratinos said both
the U.S.and the EU are making efforts to help the process out of
the current stalemate.
</P>
<P>
The peace talks on the Palestinian-Israeli track have been
deeply stranded due to Israel's firm refusal to a U.S. proposal to
pull back its troops from 13.1 percent of the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos, who paid a one-day visit to Syria Monday, left for
Lebanon Tuesday morning for talks with Lebanese President Elias
Hrawi.
</P>
<P>
Israel carved out a 1,200-square-kilometer strip in southern
Lebanon, an ally of Syria, in 1985 with the claimed aim to protect
its northern areas from guerrillas cross-border attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
