<HEADLINE> IT Plays Important Role in HK: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 28 (Xinhua) -- An official of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region said Tuesday that information
technology (IT) definitely plays a far more important part as the
city journeys forward to the next century.
</P>
<P>
Ronald Leung, chairman of the Provisional Urban Council, made
the remarks while receiving exhibits of the "Telecom World" from
the Hongkong Telecom at the Science Museum.
</P>
<P>
Leung said that television, personal computers and mobile
phones have formed an integral part of the people's life and such
advance in the communication technology has enabled people to keep
abreast of the world within doors.
</P>
<P>
"Looking ahead, with the rapid development of global
communication and the Internet, it won't be long before the era
when people can master the jobs within doors will come," Leung
said at the brief handover ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"As Hong Kong, being a cosmopolitan city and one of the biggest
financial and cargo centers in the world, journeys forward into
the 21st century, information technology definitely plays a far
more important part. It is our wish that our next generation will
appreciate the importance of communication technology through
these exhibits."
</P>
<P>
The 100-million-HK-dollar (12.8 million-U.S-dollar) "Telecom
World" was established by Hongkong Telecom in 1995. It was divided
into seven galleries dedicated to different aspects of
telecommunications. Some 100 interactive displays, exhibits and
games offered an amazing journey to the visitors from the past to
the present and to the future of telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
Plans are in hand to display these exhibits in the Science
Museum to benefit patrons to the museum by enabling them to know
more about the technology in telecommunication. 
</P>
