<HEADLINE> Yangtze Flood Threats Beijing-Kowloon Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing-Kowloon Railway,
China's south-north artery linking Beijing with Hong Kong, is now
in danger as flooding water has begun to overflow some embankments
in Yongxiu County of Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The Flood Control Headquarters in Jiujiang city has sent more
than 20,000 people to reinforce the embankments in an effort to
secure the line's smooth operation.
</P>
<P>
The water level in the Xiuhe River, which passes the county, is
rising drastically to 23.3 meters, 3.32 meters higher than the
danger level.
</P>
<P>
The related protective embankments serve as a shelter for 10.5
kilometers of the railway in the area. At one embankment, there
has occurred more than 100 breaches and landslides.
</P>
<P>
The overflow also threats 35,200 of local residents and their
property, sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
