<HEADLINE> Overseas Copyright Trade Flourishing in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The foreign copyright trade
continues to develop rapidly in the Chinese capital, according to
the Beijing Municipal Copyrights Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Beijing imported 2,066 kinds of foreign books, or some 66
percent of the national total of related imports, in 1997. The
city also exported over 200 categories of books, or close to 40
percent of the national figure.
</P>
<P>
Imports included 915 books on science and technology, 44.3
percent of the total, with the bulk of imports related to
computers.
</P>
<P>
Books on mathematics, physics, chemistry, medical, health,
geology, agriculture and statistics were also included on the
list. 
