<HEADLINE> Top Level Domain for All Citizens to Make Debut Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- A new top level domain for all
citizens, .AC, will make its debut on August 3, announced the
Internet Society (ISOC) here Monday.
</P>
<P>
All citizens will be welcome to register in .AC, said ISOC.
</P>
<P>
A number of delegates at the annual Internet Conference of the
ISOC, known as Internet Summit, have shown interest in the new
domain and said they are getting ready to register in the newest
domain on the net.
</P>
<P>
Before, some of the world's leading domain registration
companies have already signed up to offer .AC domain names,
international shorthand for Academic Community.
</P>
<P>
"Here in Japan, we have .AC.JP for academic institutions, but
there is great demand from both lecturers and students to have
personal, friendly and affordable domain names," said Takeshi
Saigoh from the research institute, Network Trend Technology.
</P>
<P>
"These domain names can be used at college and in later life to
keep in contact with college friends," he said. "We welcome the
introduction of .AC domain names to meet this demand and see the
opportunities for students around the world to use the Internet as
their communication tool for life." 
</P>
</TEXT>
