<DOCNO> XIE19980728.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Dialogue Partners Urged to Help Restore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Foreign Secretary
Domingo Siazon opened the ASEAN's Post Ministerial Conference
(PMC) with calls to the 10 ASEAN dialogue partners to help Asia
restore economic vitality and to ensure a robust global economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
"In addition to keeping their markets open, injecting new
investments and sustaining fresh financing, our dialogue partners
are urged to assume leadership in restoring economic vitality in
the region and ensuring a robust global economic growth," said
Siazon at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Siazon, who is this year's chairman of the PMC, singled out
four ASEAN major dialogue partners for their special roles in
revitalizing the Asian economy which has been battered by the
currency crisis since mid-1997.
</P>
<P>
"In particular, the United States can contribute significantly
to IMF's (International Monetary Fund) expanded capacity to
respond to financial crises by ratifying the New Arrangements to
Borrow (NAD) and the proposed quota increase in the IMF," he said.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to the Japanese government to accelerate the
implementation of the fiscal stimulus package and the reform of
its financial and income tax system.
</P>
<P>
Siazon praised China for maintaining the value of the RMB which
is widely seen as the last defense against the protracted currency
turmoil still raging in the region.
</P>
<P>
"China's firm commitment to maintain the stability of the yuan
is highly appreciated, while Europe's economic strength can
reinforce the recovery in Asia," he said.
</P>
<P>
Siazon also urged the international community to share
responsibilities in restoring economic stability in Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Considering that the financial and currency turmoil in Asia
has global roots as well as world-wide consequences, shared
international responsibility in restoring economic stability in
Asia must be recognized," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Siazon, citing the financial turmoil in Asia and the
nuclear arms race in South Asia, emphasized the need to be
ceaselessly vigilant on unpredictable events in the region.
</P>
<P>
Siazon said ASEAN will continue to cooperate with its dialogue
partners in addressing transnational concerns and social issues
such as transnational crimes and trans-boundary environmental
matters.
</P>
<P>
Among the participants attending the PMC are the foreign
ministers from the nine ASEAN member countries and the 10 ASEAN
dialogue partners.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, Malaysia,
Brunei, Vietnam, Myanmar, Laos and Indonesia. The 10 ASEAN
dialogue partners are China, the United States, Russia, Japan, the
European Union, Australia, New Zealand, Canada, India and South
Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
