<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers on Tuesday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- One hundred years after its annexation by the United States,
the Caribbean island of Porto Rico will hold a referendum on whether
to become the 51st U.S. state in four months. The islanders are more
divided than ever before over their future while the growing
strength of the Spanish community is counter-balancing the ``white''
society.
</P>
<P>
-- Ten years after famine killed 250,000 people in Sudan in 1988,
two million and a half Sudanese are again threatened with death
because of hunger caused by the civil war between the Islamic
military regime and the southern Christian rebels. Humanitarian aid
agencies estimate that from 30 to 50 percent of the food sent by the
international community are being diverted from the civilians.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- In an interview with Le Figaro, German Social-Democrat leader
Gerhard Shroeder expressed full confidence in winning the general
elections to be held in September, saying that ``all conditions are
ready for the victory.'' He said that he will establish alliance
with the Greens or a big coalition with the Christian Democrats.
</P>
<P>
-- In Sudan, the soldiers are detaining food provided by the
international aid agencies to the civilians as a weapon to wage the
war. Despite the biggest food releasing operation launched by the
international community in history, some 700,000 people are dying of
hunger in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
