<HEADLINE> Rainfall Along Yangtze Subsiding: Meteorologist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Rainfall will subside along the
Yangtze River area in the coming few days, and there will be no
torrential rains on a larger scale, said Tang Huifang, deputy
director of the Central Meteorological Station.
</P>
<P>
However, the official told Xinhua in an interview today that
some parts of the area will possibly have torrential rains, as no
signs so far have shown that rainfall in the river valley will
stop until August 1-2.
</P>
<P>
"We should not relax our vigilance even if it is small amount
of rainfall because the Yangtze River has been threatened by a
serious flood," she warned.
</P>
<P>
Tropical storms or typhoons will not affect the river area in
the coming five days, she said, adding that her station will
follow closely the weather changes in the area as there are still
some unpredictable factors therein.  
</P>
