<HEADLINE> 7 Killed, 38 Injured in Traffic Accident in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Four Germans and three Dutch people
were killed when two Dutch coaches and a German tour bus collided
on a highway in southeast France Monday night, Agence
France-Presse (AFP) reported.
</P>
<P>
Among the dead was a little girl from Germany, and eight people
were seriously injured, including a boy whose arm was severed,
while 30 others got slight injuries, AFP quoted rescue workers as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The three buses, carrying a total of 139 passengers, crashed
into one another at the head of a traffic jam triggered by the
overturning of a truck on the A7 highway near Montelimar.
</P>
<P>
But all the passengers in one of the Dutch buses remained
unhurt, while the arrear part of the German bus was completely
damaged, resulting in most of the casualties.
</P>
<P>
Helicopters were reportedly used in rescue operations to send
those seriously injured to hospitals in the nearby cities of
Montelimar, Lyon and Valence. 
</P>
