Hotel where the leaders are staying and roads within the Colombo
Municipal Council Area have been decorated with flags of the SAARC
member nations.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers from the SAARC states closed their two-day
meeting Tuesday afternoon to prepare the agenda for the Summit
which groups Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives, Nepal,
Pakistan and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
SAARC, formed in December 1985, aims to promote regional
cooperation in economic, social, cultural and other fields.
