<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Decreases in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
re-exports, domestic exports and imports registered decreases in
June on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed in the external trade figures for June 1998
released Tuesday by the Census and Statistics Department of Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The value of total exports (comprising re-exports and domestic
exports) decreased by 2.0 percent in June 1998 over a year earlier
to 116.7 billion HK dollars (15 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Within this total, the value of re-exports decreased by 2.1
percent to 99.0 billion HK dollars (12.7 billion U.S. dollars),
while the value of domestic exports decreased by 1.2 percent to
17.7 billion HK dollars (2.3 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The value of imports decreased by 6.4 percent in June 1998 over
a year earlier to 123.3 billion HK dollars (15.8 billion U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
A visible trade deficit of 6.6 billion HK dollars (0.85 billion
U.S. dollars) was recorded in June 1998. This was much smaller
than the deficit of 12.7 billion HK dollars recorded in June 1997.
</P>
<P>
For the first half of 1998 as a whole, the value of total
exports was lower by 2.1 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
A Government Secretariat spokesman noted that the year-on-year
decrease in the value of total exports recorded in June 1998 was
smaller than those in the preceding two months.
</P>
<P>
For the first half of 1998 as a whole, the value of total
exports fell only moderately over a year earlier, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that the visible trade deficit showed a
narrowing in the first half of 1998 compared to a year earlier, as
the value of imports fell considerably along with the moderation
in domestic demand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
