<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Records Marginal Increase in Power Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Power stations in China generated
some 530 billion kwh of power in the first half of this year,
according to the China National Power Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The hydropower industry contributed 88 billion, up 5.4 percent
from the 1997 period, with the output for the nuclear power
industry growing by 17 percent to 7.1 billion kwh.
</P>
<P>
Experts attributed the period's slower growth in power output
to relatively high winter temperatures and heavy spring and summer
rains.
</P>
<P>
The decrease in industrial power consumption during the period
was also attributed to the one to two percentage point drop in
power generation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
