<HEADLINE> Flooding Fails to Interrupt Bridge Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The main part of the Dongting
Bridge, a major project in central China's Hunan Province, was
recently completed against a backdrop of heavy flooding.
</P>
<P>
The main part of the national construction project, located at
the convergence of Dongting Lake and the Yangtze River, was
completed despite heavy flooding in the area in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
The local government attributes the achievement to the
dedication and painstaking efforts of the construction team.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the bridge commenced in December 1996 and the
project will become fully operational in October 1999. The overall
project will be completed at a total cost of 500 million yuan.
</P>
</TEXT>
