<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction Project Market Opens in Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- A construction project market
started operation last Sunday in Chongqing, China's newest and
largest municipality.
</P>
<P>
The market, born amidst a construction boom, will provide a
formal venue for contractors to bid on construction projects
funded by the municipal government and local state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The market will also be responsible for quality supervision,
price and construction management, and contract authorization.
</P>
<P>
Future plans call for the market to handle all types of
construction projects available to Chinese and overseas developers
operating in both the state and non-state sectors.
</P>
<P>
However, projects involving state secrets or disaster relief
will be excluded from the market's scope of operations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
