<DOCNO> XIE19980728.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia, China Share Medals in Goodwill Game Diving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Russia took the gold medals in
the men's 10-meter platform and women's 3-meter spring-board
synchronized diving while China claimed the two silvers and one
bronze at the Goodwill Games in Long Island, New York on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Dimitry Sautin won the men's gold by scoring a total
of 665.49 points, leading all the way but the second round in the
ten-round diving at the Nassau County Goodwill Games Swimming and
Diving Center Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Sautin, who also won the title of the 3-meter spring-board on
Sunday, gained three over-eighty marks with 87.36 points, the
highest in the night, in his last dive with back one and one half
somersault three and one half twists.
</P>
<P>
"You have to work hard, work, work, work and work again. That
is the simplest secret," Sautin told reporters after the
competition on the secret of his success.
</P>
<P>
The second place was moving back and forth between the two
Chinese divers, Tian Liang and Sun Shuwei. Tian, who made an
impressive dive in the ninth attempt that added him 83.52 points
to surpass his teammate Sun, claimed the silver medal.
</P>
<P>
Sun, who was in the second place from the sixth round to eighth
round, failed in the last but one round in which he just got 34.68
points. With a total of 598.80 points, he bagged the bronze medal.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 3-meter spring-board synchro diving, Russia's
Yuliya Pakhalina and Irina Lashko claimed the gold medal by edging
off the Chinese pair, Zhang Jing and Zeng Bingxuan.
</P>
<P>
The Russian girls were 1.8 points ahead of the Chinese girls
after the second round. But the Chinese beat the Russians in the
third round by 5.6 points.
</P>
<P>
However, Pakhalina and Lashko's 67.50 and 65.52 points
performances in the last two rounds made their score about 5.00
points more than the Chinese divers.
</P>
<P>
Also, the Chinese pair won the silver by just 1.08 points
advantage against the third place finisher, Germany's Conny
Schmalfuss and Simona Koch, who dived a total of 282.72 points in
the five rounds.
</P>
<P>
Eleven divers from five countries competed in the men's event
and six pairs from five nations performed in the women's synchro
Monday night. The lower place finishers were from the United
States, Mexico, and Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980728.0223 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan to Revive Economy Through Fiscal, Financial, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government will
implement a series of fiscal, financial and tax policies without
delay for the recovery of the country's faltering economy, a
senior Japanese official said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the plenary session of the ASEAN's Post Ministerial
Conference, Japanese State Secretary for Foreign Affairs Masahiko
Komura said that Tokyo recognized the hastening of its economic
recovery is vital not only to its own economy but also to the
Asian and the world economies.
</P>
<P>
According to Komura, the centerpiece of the fiscal policy is a
package of Comprehensive Economic Measures under which
governmental expense will be increased by about 12 trillion yen
(90 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
As to the financial policy, he said, Japan will make
comprehensive and detailed efforts toward "aggressive disposal of
non-performing loans and the stability and revitalization of the
financial system."
</P>
<P>
Japan's Financial Supervision Agency is now inspecting the
major 19 banks, and necessary measures will be strictly taken
according to the results of the inspection, Komura said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, the government will carry out a fundamental
reform of tax systems which will include a reduction of the
effective rate of corporation tax to the international standard.
</P>
<P>
The personal income tax will be also reduced from next year as
a result of the permanent reform of the system after studying all
the points at the issue.
</P>
<P>
"In order to keep the Japanese economy truly active, it is
necessary to implement economic and other structural reforms in
many fields other than the above-mentioned fields," he said.
</P>
<P>
The international community has urged Japan to stabilize the
yen and conduct economic reforms to get the economy back on to the
growth path in order to curb the financial crisis still raging in
Asia.
</P>
<P>
The recent devaluation of the yen against the U.S. dollar has
triggered another round of currency turmoil in Southeast and East
Asia.
</P>
<P>
Komura, whose country is an ASEAN dialogue partner, and his
counterparts from the other 9 ASEAN dialogue partners are here
attending the two-day ASEAN's Post Ministerial Conference.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980728.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.5 on the
Richter scale hit Baicheng County in the western part of northwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region at 12:51 (04:51 GMT) today.
</P>
<P>
According to the China Seismological Bureau, the epicenter of the
quake was located at 41.8 degrees north latitude and 81.6 east
longitude.
</P>
<P>
As the epicenter was located at an area 30 kilometers southwest
of the county seat, some walls of the houses in the town were
collapsed, preliminary reports said.
</P>
<P>
No casualties have been reported so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
