<HEADLINE> Iran Expresses Concern About Kosovo Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Iran has expressed concern about
intensification of armed conflicts in Kosovo in recent days,
calling on the international community to put an end to the
fighting, the official news agency IRNA reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi said on
Monday that continued armed clashes and considerable buildup of
armed forces in the Kosovo region, along with sluggish diplomatic
efforts, have brought about a vast crisis engulfing the region.
</P>
<P>
He said that the crisis would lead to nothing but civilian
losses and homelessness of tens of thousands of local people.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the Serb security forces and
the separatist Kosovo Liberation Army seriously clashed last
weekend, leaving heavy casualties from both sides.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian spokesman called on international circles to pay
due attention to the need of putting an end to the current
conflicts in Kosovo as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Iran, as the current chairman of the Organization of the
Islamic Conference, urges extended international cooperation in a
bid to end the current miserable situation through diplomatic
efforts, he said.
</P>
<P>
Touching on the situation in Georgia, Mohammad expressed
regret over the failure of the third round of talks in Geneva
between representatives of Georgia and the separatist Abkhazia
region.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that discussion would continue to reach a
peaceful solution to the problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
