<HEADLINE> Australian Minister Stunned by Samaranch's Comments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Australian Sports Minister Andrew
Thomson said on Tuesday he was astonished by a latest report
concerning the stance on doping of the International Olympic
Committee President Juan Antonio Samaranch.
</P>
<P>
A Spanish newspaper had quoted Samaranch as saying some banned
drugs could be legalised, a much softer stand than before.
</P>
<P>
But Thomson told Australian Broadcasting Corporation (ABC)
radio: "It just leaves me gobsmacked (amazed)."
</P>
<P>
He added: "But let me be blunt, the Australian government will
do everything we can to stop cheating in sport. Doping, that is
taking drugs in order to enhance one's performance, in order to
cheat on one's competitors -- that's exactly as I describe, it's
cheating."
</P>
<P>
The IOC issued a statement on Monday saying it would stage a
world conference on doping in Switzerland in January. 
</P>
