<DOCNO> XIE19980728.0234 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya to Control Inflation Rate at 5% </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The Central Bank of Kenya (CBK)
is aiming at reducing the inflation rate to about five percent in
the next half of this year, a target it failed to achieve in the
first half.
</P>
<P>
Inflation remained higher than expected in the first half of
1998, despite a sustained reduction in monetary expansion, the
Daily Nation newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to a six month's monetary policy statement released
Monday, the target will be made easier by the government's
success in a balanced budget in the current 1998/99 (June/July)
financial year.
</P>
<P>
Late last year, the bank predicted that inflation would remain
lower than five percent by the end of June, 1998, two points up
from last June's 4.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
"With the successful implementation of the monetary policy,
CBK will be contributing effectively to improving the economic
performance of the country," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The underlying inflation (inflation that can be controlled
through monetary policy) in the east African country assumed a
strong upward trend towards the end of June.
</P>
<P>
The underlying inflation rose to 11.3 percent in June 1998
from 4.6 percent in June 1997.
</P>
<P>
The overall month-on-month inflation, however, eased in the
second half of the 1997/98 fiscal year to 7.4 percent by June
1998, from 12.8 percent in June 1997.
</P>
<P>
CBK says the rate of inflation rose because there was less
than expected supply of goods and services following poor
economic performance in the 1997/98 year.
</P>
<P>
The CBK report said that food supply was partially affected by
wide-spread drought in the late 1996 and early 1997 and the
disruption of supplies by the El Nino related rains and floods.
</P>
<P>
"This more than offset the dampening effect of a sustained
slow monetary expansion during the year," said the report.
</P>
<P>
The report also attributed the increased inflation to the
upward adjustment of the value added tax. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980728.0235 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Defines Business Operations of Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Ministry of
Education said today that education is a public sector and China
will prohibit any school from using its status to earn exorbitant
profits from students.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China is currently introducing experimental
reform to allow private institutions and social organizations to
operate schools previously managed by the government.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the development of the education sector has been
hindered because of a lack of funding has prompted the government
to encourage various entities to operate schools.
</P>
<P>
Some experts predict that privatization will quickly merge with
China's education sector.
</P>
<P>
However, the spokesman refuted the statements. He also pointed
out that some schools operated or funded by private institutions
have charged high tuition fees to increase profits. "The practice
must be stopped," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the ministry will tightly control the number
of private schools or related institutions using private funds,
and will set ceilings on the salaries of the teachers in private
schools to make sure that they are not too higher than those of
teachers in government-run schools.
</P>
<P>
He also said the ministry will at the same time ensure the
protection of state property. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980728.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Divers Claim Two Golds at Goodwill Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Russia took two gold medals in
the diving competition, while the United States claimed the
women's soccer title at the 1998 Goodwill Games here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Russia swept the final two diving top honors by winning the
men's platform and the women's 3-meter synchronized springboard.
Dmitry Sautin, the Olympic and world champion, proved he was
unbeatable in the platform, leading all the way with big margins
to collect 665.49 points.
</P>
<P>
China's Tian Liang and Sun Shuwei, who took the platform
synchronized title last week, failed to pose real threat to the
Russian. Tian collected 623.01 to finish second to Sun's 598.80.
</P>
<P>
Sautin opened with 41.76 in his first of ten dives, leading the
field with a slight gap in front of Sun's 41.28. Tian surged into
the leading position after the second round and hanging tough with
Sautin on the next two rounds.
</P>
<P>
Sautin dropped Tian for good with three straight excellent
dives on the next three outings before recording the highest score
of 87.36 to wrap up the battle.
</P>
<P>
"Sautin is still the king who reign the platform now. We have
to work hard to catch up with him," China's team leader Li Dazheng
admitted after the competition.
</P>
<P>
Irina Lashko and Yuliya Pakhalina subdued China's Zhang Jing
and Zeng Bingxuan to win the women's 3-meter synchronized
springboard with a small edge, registering 289.62 against 283.80
from the Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Lashko, a mother of two who has been a world class diver during
this decade, appeared too awesome to be beaten in the race.
</P>
<P>
The Russian tandem led the first two rounds and regained the
lead in the final two dives to upset the Chinese pair on the
closing day of the diving competition. Russia and China each raked
up four gold medals out of the ten events.
</P>
<P>
The day's another gold was won by the United States women's
soccer team, who were also the Olympic champions. They beat the
Olympic runners-up China 2-0 to land the gold medal.
</P>
<P>
Mia Hamm scored twice in the second half at 66th and 87th
minutes. It was the first Goodwill Games' title for the United
States, which got its 38th consecutive victory on home soil.
</P>
<P>
"I'm satisfied with the win. China is an excellent team. The
game was a balance affair for a while, and we just had to find a
way to win," commended Tony DiCicco, head coach of the United
States team.
</P>
<P>
"One of the characteristics of this team is that we are very
mentally strong, and tonight we were able to win with some
mentally tough players."
</P>
<P>
Forward Hamm said: "This was a wonderful crowd. It was
unbelievable. It was a tremendous effort."
</P>
<P>
China's coach Ma Yuanan said: "The United States team is the
strongest squad in the world, they deserved the win. We lost to
them at the Olympics in 1996, and tonight, they beat us again. I
hope we can have a chance to meet in the final of the world
championships next year."
</P>
<P>
Boxing competition started today but no medals were produced.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
