<HEADLINE> China Fulfills Oil and Natural Gas Output Targets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- China basically fulfilled targets
by recovering more than 78 million tons of crude oil and 7.2
billion cu.m. of natural gas during the first six months of the
year, including both onshore and offshore production.
</P>
<P>
The figures were jointly released by the China National
Petroleum Corp., China Petrochemical Corp. and China Offshore
Petroleum Corporation.
</P>
<P>
China's oil industry has been hard hit by the financial turmoil
in Southeast Asia which has led to sharp reductions in
international oil prices and battered China's oil exports.
</P>
<P>
The supply of crude oil and finished oil products on the
domestic market has exceeded demand and inventories have
soared. The industry was forced to cap numerous wells during the
period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
