<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Leaves for Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina left here Tuesday morning for Colombo, Sri Lanka, to attend
the 10th SAARC (South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation)
summit in Colombo scheduled to open Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hasina is leading a 17-member delegation, including Foreign
Minister Abdus Samad Azad and Foreign Secretary Mustafizur Rahman,
for the three-day summit.
</P>
<P>
Besides delivering a speech at the summit, the prime minister
is expected to hold bilateral talks with heads of government and
state of SAARC countries on the sideline of the summit.
</P>
<P>
She will meet with Indian Prime Minster Atal Behari Vajpayee
and Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif Wednesday, and return
home Friday evening, officials said.
</P>
<P>
SAARC, which was founded in 1985, now groups Bangladesh,
Bhutan, India, the Maldives, Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka.
</P>
