<HEADLINE> Li Peng Shows Concern About Yangtze Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), has shown great
concern about the flooding along the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
Early this morning, the NPC chairman, who is also a Standing
Committee member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of
China Central Committee, called the State Flood Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters in Beijing, asking about the details
of the flooding along the river, China's longest, and about the
protection of the main stream, Dongting and Poyang lakes along it.
</P>
<P>
He was very much concerned about flood control efforts in
Wuhan, a central China hub and capital of Hubei Province, and
Jiujiang city of Jiangxi Province at the middle reaches of the
river in particular.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he also asked about the flooding of the Songhua
and Nenjiang rivers in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng showed great concern about the armymen and civilians
fighting the current flooding. He called on all the localities to
strictly follow China's Law on Flood Control as well as
instructions from President Jiang Zemin in fighting the flooding,
and win the success in their fight against the flooding under
the leadership of the Party and the State Council.  
</P>
