<HEADLINE> Third Yangtze Flood Crest Passing Wuhan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- The third Yangtze River flood
crest is right now passing Wuhan, a central China hub and capital
of Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin showed great concern about the
passing, calling on the battling armymen and civilians there to go
all out to fight the flooding and secure the city.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader made the call early this morning when he
called on Vice Premier Wen Jiabao, who is now in the city
directing flood control efforts.
</P>
<P>
Flood control along the river, China's longest, is now
critical, with the third flood crest is passing Wuhan at the
moment.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president was very much concerned about the flood
situation there. In his phone call, he asked about the details of
the flooding, calling on all the soldiers and people now fighting
flooding to continue their effort and win greater successes.
</P>
<P>
This morning, Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao came to a section of the
Yangtze River bank in Wuhan, communicating the instructions from
the president to the armymen and people there who pledged to
protect Wuhan and nearby two cities at any cost. 
</P>
