<HEADLINE> Chilean President to Visit Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo Frei
is scheduled to visit Panama in September to discuss issues
related to the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA).
</P>
<P>
A source here said Frei, the first Chilean president to visit
Panama, will also join there with some other Latin American
leaders at the 12th summit meeting of the group in early September.
</P>
<P>
Since 1996, Panama and Chile have been negotiating with the
NAFTA members, currently the United States, Canada and Mexico, to
acquire the membership of the regional bloc.
</P>
<P>
NAFTA, established in January 1994, is expected to expand to a
Pan-American free trade zone.
</P>
<P>
And between Panama and Chile, annual trade is about 46 million
U.S. dollars, excluding 6 million dollars of merchandise that
Chile buys from the free trade zone in Colon, of Panama. 
