<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Economic Brief News from Latin America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The following is major
economic news briefs from Latin American countries in recent days.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Europe has replaced Brazil as the number one
buyer of Uruguay's meat during the first 200 days of this year.
</P>
<P>
During the period, Uruguay exported 32,962 tons of meat to the
European market, down 7 percent from the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country's meat exports to Brazil totaled 30,211
tons, a 27.5 percent decrease from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- Costa Rica's banana export earnings in the first
six months this year totaled 293.63 million U.S. dollars, up 0.72
percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics showed that the earnings amounted to 11.68
percent of the country's total revenues from overseas sales of
fruit in January through June.
</P>
<P>
Banana is the most important farm produce for exportation in
Costa Rica, the world's second largest banana producer following
Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- The revenues of the Panamanian government in the
year's first six months totaled 805 million dollars, 31 million
dollars more than that in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance and Treasury said the government
collected revenues of 554 million dollars from public sectors and
200 million dollars from private sectors.
</P>
<P>
The earnings of import taxes reached 112 million dollars, while
the government-run enterprises made a profit of 99 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Brazil's automobile exports in the first six
months this year was up 18 percent from the same period last year,
said a report of the Brazilian Association of Car Manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
The report said the country sold 211,294 units of automobiles
at the international market in January through June, compared to
179,307 units sold in the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
