<HEADLINE> Albania Protests Over Alleged Yugoslavia Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Albanian Foreign Ministry on
Monday presented a note to Yugoslavia protesting about what it
called the "threat posed against Albania's sovereignty and
integrity of territory."
</P>
<P>
The note, presented to the Yugoslav Charge d'Affaires in
Albania, protested about the alleged firing by Yugoslavian
frontier guards at the Kukes area on Albania's side of the border
with Kosovo, early on Sunday morning. The note said it posed a
direct threat to Albania's sovereignty and integrity of territory.
</P>
<P>
Sources in Albania's ministry of internal affairs said the
firing lasted about 15 minutes. It left bullet holes on buildings
and forced women and children of some villages to move away.
</P>
<P>
The note said Yugoslavia's act could lead to undesirable
results, and demanded that authorities involved stop this kind of
offense immediately, and promise no such events would happen again.
</P>
<P>
Until now there have been no reports of Yugoslavia's reaction
to the protest.
</P>
<P>
As the Kosovo crisis accelerates, incidents on the
Albania-Yugoslavia border have increased. But so far there have
been no direct clashes between the two country's armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Also Monday, seven members of the so-called Kosovo Liberation
Army (KLA) were killed in a clash on the border between Yugoslavia
and Albania, reported Yugoslav news agency Tanjug.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the media center in the provincial capital
Pristina was quoted as saying the ethnic Albanian separatists were
killed by Yugoslav border guards in a cross-fire while attempting
to flee to neighboring Albania.
</P>
<P>
Bloodsheds and casualties occurred constantly over the past
days since the Serbian security force intensified its offensives
to drive KLA rebels out from the troubled province of the Republic
of Serbia, in the Yugoslav Federation.
</P>
<P>
Belgrade says troops are deployed in securing the bordering
area, and therefore the military was not involved in the fighting
between security forces and ethnic Albanian guerrillas inside
Kosovo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
