<HEADLINE>     S 7733 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rains and flooding
over the past 10 days have caused direct economic losses of 1.7
billion yuan in one prefecture in east China's Jiangxi Province,
according to reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The floods, never seen in history, have destroyed 463,600
houses and inundated 246,700 ha of farmland and completely
destroyed crops on 109,900 ha. in Shangrao Prefecture. More than
2,660 industrial enterprises have either ceased production or are
operating below capacity and the lives of 1.55 million people have
been affected.
</P>
<P>
By 2:00 pm yesterday, water levels on Poyang Lake were above 22
meters, or more than 3 m above the danger mark.
</P>
<P>
Water levels on the Xinjiang, Le'An, and Changjiang rivers have
all passed the danger mark and are continuing to rise.
</P>
<P>
Embankments at 7 locations were in danger of collapsing and
466,300 people in 2,337 villages were being threatened by the
floods.
</P>
<P>
Local Communist Party and government officials have organized
800,000 people who are working day and night to repair river dikes
and send in rescue materials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
