<HEADLINE> Brazilian Coach Fired with Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Brazil national coach
Marlo Zagallo and the whole staff were fired by the Brazilian
Soccer Confederation here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The saga will continue, and you'll have the last installment
when they name the new coach," Zagallo was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Zagallo coached the national team over 148 games in two terms,
including 107 victories, 29 ties and 12 losses.
</P>
<P>
Zagallo's first game as coach was in 1970 and claimed the
title in the World Cup in Mexico. He led Brazil to the World Cup
crown again in the 1994 tournament.
</P>
<P>
However, his team lost to France in this year's World Cup
final, and had to conceded the silver medal in poor forms.
</P>
<P>
The national team's new coach will be named on August 31.
</P>
