<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Prices Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The average price of OPEC's basket
of seven crudes increased to 12.12 dollars per barrel last week,
15 U.S. cents more than the previous week, the Secretariat of the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
OPEC's average price is 12.79 dollars per barrel in the past
six months of this year, 7.89 dollars lower than the 18.68 dollars
of last year.
</P>
<P>
Crude oil prices on the international oil market have been
rising slowly since OPEC twice lowered the daily oil output
limitation in March and June.
</P>
<P>
OPEC has set the benchmark price of oil per barrel at 21
dollars. 
</P>
