<HEADLINE> Cross-Strait Trade Up In First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 28 (Xinhua) -- Trade between the Chinese mainland
and Taiwan region reached 9.61 billion U.S. dollars in the first
half of this year, up 9.2 percent from the same period of 1997,
according to the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chinese mainland's export to Taiwan was 1.8 billion U.S.
dollars, up 22.2 percent, and its import from the region,
7.8 billion U.S. dollars, up 6.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Trade with Taiwan accounted for 6.3 percent of the mainland's
total and Taiwan is the mainland's fifth largest trading partner.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Taiwan investment in the mainland declined
substantially in the first six months, with new Taiwan-funded
projects down 3.26 percent to 1,336, contractual investment down
8.41 percent to 1.2 billion U.S. dollars, and actual investment
down 8.6 percent to be 1.47 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last month, there were 39,821 Taiwan-invested
projects on the mainland with an actual investment of 19.8 billion
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
