<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norway Snatches Bronze in Women' Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Norway carried home with the
bronze medal for the 1998 Goodwill Games women's soccer after
winning the penalty kick shoot-out 4-2 against Denmark here Monday
evening.
</P>
<P>
The final scores were 5-3. The two teams were tied 1-1 at the
end of the regulation.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Lehn Unni of Norway scored the first goal in the
20th minute, with the assistance of her team-mate Pettersen
Marianne.
</P>
<P>
In the 82nd minute, midfielder Anne Nielsen managed to
equalized for Denmark.
</P>
<P>
During the penalty shoot-out, the Danes missed the first and
fourth kick and their counterparts sent in all the four.
</P>
<P>
The United States and China will compete for the gold medal
later Monday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
