<HEADLINE> IOC to Hold First Doping Conference in '99 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The International Olympic Committee
(IOC) has decided to hold the first international conference on
doping in Lausanne, Switzerland, in January 1999, the organization
announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
IOC President Juan Samaranch said that he expected the
conference to produce important results, in particular, a clear
definition of doping.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the IOC's determination against doping was greater
than ever.
</P>
<P>
The IOC said its decision to hold the international conference
on doping was aimed at placing emphasis on protecting athletes'
health while fully observing the principles of sports and medical
ethics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
