-- Health, education and childcare will be the only exclusions
from the Australian government's 10 percent goods and services
tax, while food and housing will be fully taxed.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Morning Herald:
</P>
<P>
-- Rural pressure and the political impact of One Nation Party
have forced the major banks in Australia to announce measures
aimed at placating customers upset over cuts to services.
</P>
<P>
The Age:
</P>
<P>
-- The international sporting drugs controversy deepened
Monday, with an admission by a leading Australian athlete of drug
use and a startling claim by the world's most powerful sporting
figure Juan Antonio Samaranch endorsing the use of performance
enhancing substances.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review:
</P>
<P>
-- The Australian coal-mining union is planning industry-wide
strike action in Australia's leading export sector to protest
against falling coal prices and job losses resulting from
"suicidal" competition among domestic producers. 
</P>
