<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China: UN Reform Is a Matter Concerning Entire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Addressing the U.N. Economic and Social Council, Chinese
Deputy Representative to the United Nations Sheng Guofang said
consensus reached on relevant issues only after extensive
discussions with the participation of the member states can
withstand the test of time.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Sheng said with regard to the subsidiary bodies which
have really been inefficient and have failed to play their due
role, it is not adequate to eliminate them or incorporate
them into some other bodies.
</P>
<P>
Sheng said doubled efforts should be designed to reach the targets
and concrete measures be taken for improvement so as to
achieve the objective of ensuring the fundamental institutional
balance of the U.N. on one hand, and enhancing role and efficiency
of the relevant bodies on the other.
</P>
<P>
Sheng said the reform of the United Nations is a process, and
time should be allowed for new reform measures be tested in the
process of actual implementation, so that member states can
objectively sum up experiences and decide on the best future
courses of action on this basis.
</P>
<P>
Sheng said adoption of reform measures is only a first step
in the efforts to achieve the objectives of revitalizing the
role of the U.N. in the economic and social fields. Without
adequate resources, no reform plan will achieve this objective.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
